News

Longtime president of Devault Foods names successor








        Show from left are Tom Fillippo, Bret Black and Thomas W. Fillippo of Devault Foods. The eastern Chester County company announced a management transition on Tuesday.
        










  By Staff Report




                                            Posted: 
                                        01/17/17, 4:41 PM EST
|
Updated: on 01/17/2017

# Comments









CHARLESTOWN >> Devault Foods, a portion-controlled meat preparation and packing company, announced Tuesday changes in top executive positions.



Longtime President Tom Fillippo is becoming chairman of the board. He will be replaced as president by Brett Black, the current chief operating officer. Fillippo’s son, Thomas W. Fillippo, has been promoted to executive vice president of the 70-year-old firm that provides products like burgers, meatballs, Philly steaks, sausages, steaks and chops.



“Devault Foods is rapidly growing into an unrivaled company with operational excellence,” said Tom Fillippo, who has been president of the company since 1970. “I have strong confidence in Brett, Thomas and the leadership team to successfully carry the Fillippo family legacy into the distant future.”



The company is committed to continuous improvement in operations, developing new trends, expanding product categories and capturing market share in growing geographic markets, it said in its announcement Tuesday.




Advertisement




Devault Foods noted that change is the new constant in any business today with technology developments, globalization and new competitors disrupting traditional business models.



“No business lasts over the long haul if it can’t reinvent itself to address the evolving preferences and needs of its customers.” Black said. “Devault Foods is in a strong position to succeed and the time is ripe to aggressively pursue the company’s new goals.”



To contact Business Editor Brian McCullough, call 610-235-2655 or send an email to bmccullough@dailylocal.com.





